    "content": "<p>It was spectacular. It was magical. And it in no way changed my feelings about the amplified musicals I&#8217;d seen and enjoyed for years. I had been captivated by almost every one of those shows, and the use of microphones hadn&#8217;t kept me from falling in love with <!-- a href=\"http:\/\/tommytune.com\" -->Tommy Tune<!-- \/a --> <strong>(REFERENCE ICON) <a href=\"http:\/\/www.tommytune.com\/\">Tommy Tune<\/a> is a Broadway legend.<\/strong> at the age of 12 (no, that didn&#8217;t work out too well) or crying my eyes out at the end of <!-- a href=\"http:\/\/www.falsettos.net\/\" -->Falsettos<!-- \/a --> <strong>(REFERENCE ICON) <a href=\"http:\/\/www.falsettos.net\/\">Falsettos<\/a> was a musical that ran on Broadway in 1992 and 1993.<\/strong> at the age of 21.<\/p>\n",
