    "content": "<p>The continued hand-wringing over how amplification has damaged the musical reminds me of the hand-wringing over how the Internet has damaged human communications. A new technology comes along and makes some voices louder: we&#8217;re told that once we no longer have to work at paying attention, we stop listening. We&#8217;re told we won&#8217;t appreciate nuances that get lost when we turn up the volume.<\/p>\n",
    "excerpt": "The continued hand-wringing over how amplification has damaged the musical reminds me of the hand-wringing over how the Internet has damaged human communications. A new technology comes along and makes some voices louder: we&#8217;re told that once we no longer &hellip; <a href=\"http:\/\/book.hyko.org\/1970-10-05\/\">Continue reading <span class=\"meta-nav\">&rarr;<\/span><\/a>",
