    "title_plain": "Listening to the Voice That Says It&#039;s OK to Be Online &sect; 6",
    "content": "<p>We&#8217;ve turned up the volume, all right: the volume of e-mail, the volume of information, the volume of ways we have to connect. And it can get very loud online. But talk to most musical theater-lovers, including those of us who regard our affection for <!-- LINK IS OUTDATED a class=\"zem_slink\" title=\"Stephen Sondheim\" rel=\"myspaceeverything\" href=\"http:\/\/www.myspace.com\/everything\/stephen-sondheim\" -->Stephen Sondheim<!-- \/a --> <strong>(REFERENCE ICON) &#8220;Stephen Sondheim was born in New York in 1930, and is widely acknowledged as the most innovative, most influential and most important composer and lyricist in modern Broadway history.&#8221; FURTHER READING <a href=\"http:\/\/www.sondheim.org\/about\/about-stephen-sondheim\">The Stephen Sondheim Society<\/a><\/strong> as proof that we are<em> serious<\/em> musical theater people, and they will probably confess that they loved <!-- a class=\"zem_slink\" title=\"LES MISERABLES (French) The first one :  PARIS 1980 - Robert HOSSEIN - (Archives Rene-Louis BARON)\" rel=\"youtube\" href=\"http:\/\/www.youtube.com\/watch?v=Q7ppd66UURg\" -->Les Miz<!-- \/a -->, <strong>(REFERENCE ICON) <a class=\"zem_slink\" title=\"LES MISERABLES (French) The first one :  PARIS 1980 - Robert HOSSEIN - (Archives Rene-Louis BARON)\" href=\"http:\/\/www.youtube.com\/watch?v=Q7ppd66UURg\" rel=\"youtube\">Les Miserables<\/a> is a musical based on the novel by Victor Hugo.<\/strong> mikes and all. Loud is loud, but it isn&#8217;t necessarily bad. It&#8217;s just another kind of stimulation, another kind of spectacle.<\/p>\n",
    "excerpt": "We&#8217;ve turned up the volume, all right: the volume of e-mail, the volume of information, the volume of ways we have to connect. And it can get very loud online. But talk to most musical theater-lovers, including those of us &hellip; <a href=\"http:\/\/book.hyko.org\/1970-10-06\/\">Continue reading <span class=\"meta-nav\">&rarr;<\/span><\/a>",
