    "title_plain": "10 Ways SPAM Taught Us to Focus Our Attention &sect; 2",
    "content": "<p>It&#8217;s customary to <!-- a href=\"http:\/\/www.ukprogressive.co.uk\/happy-30th-birthday-spam-%E2%80%93-damn-you-gary-thuerk\/article238.html\" -->curse the name of Thuerk<!-- \/a -->, <strong>(REFERENCE ICON) FURTHER READING <a href=\"http:\/\/www.ukprogressive.co.uk\/happy-30th-birthday-spam-%E2%80%93-damn-you-gary-thuerk\/article238.html\">Happy 30th Birthday SPAM \u2013 Damn You Gary Thuerk!<\/a><\/strong> though Thuerk himself uses <!-- a href=\"http:\/\/www.linkedin.com\/in\/fatherespam\" -->fatherespam as his LinkedIn profile URL<!-- \/a -->,  and prominently cites his role in creating spam as a professional credential. (Guess he decided to embrace it sometime <!-- a href=\"http:\/\/www.esecurityplanet.com\/trends\/article.php\/3438651\/Father-of-Spam-Speaks-Out-on-His-Legacy.htm\" -->after this interview<!-- \/a -->.) <strong>(REFERENCE ICON) Thuerk refers to himself as one of the original spammers. FURTHER READING <a href=\"http:\/\/www.esecurityplanet.com\/trends\/article.php\/3438651\/Father-of-Spam-Speaks-Out-on-His-Legacy.htm\">Father of Spam Speaks Out on His Legacy<\/a><\/strong> But I think that Gary Thuerk is owed more than <!-- a href=\"http:\/\/www.lockergnome.com\/news\/2004\/11\/22\/got-spam-thank-gary-thuerk\/\" -->a sarcastic thank you<!-- \/a -->.<strong>(REFERENCE ICON) FURTHER READING <a href=\"http:\/\/www.lockergnome.com\/news\/2004\/11\/22\/got-spam-thank-gary-thuerk\/\">Got Spam? Thank Gary Thuerk<\/a><\/strong><\/p>\n",
    "excerpt": "It&#8217;s customary to curse the name of Thuerk, (REFERENCE ICON) FURTHER READING Happy 30th Birthday SPAM \u2013 Damn You Gary Thuerk! though Thuerk himself uses fatherespam as his LinkedIn profile URL, and prominently cites his role in creating spam as &hellip; <a href=\"http:\/\/book.hyko.org\/1970-09-02\/\">Continue reading <span class=\"meta-nav\">&rarr;<\/span><\/a>",
