    "title": "10 Ways SPAM Taught Us to Focus Our Attention &sect; 3",
    "title_plain": "10 Ways SPAM Taught Us to Focus Our Attention &sect; 3",
    "content": "<p>After all, spam &#8212; now estimated at <!-- a href=\"http:\/\/www.securelist.com\/en\/analysis\/204792167\/Spam_report_February_2011\" -->more than 75% of e-mail traffic<!-- \/a --> <strong>(REFERENCE ICON) According to the Spam Report, 2011. FURTHER READING <a href=\"http:\/\/www.securelist.com\/en\/analysis\/204792167\/Spam_report_February_2011\">Spam report: February 2011<\/a><\/strong> &#8212; has been one of the major drivers of online innovation. To cope with <!-- a href=\"http:\/\/articles.latimes.com\/2003\/may\/11\/business\/fi-spam11\" -->&#8220;Pandora&#8217;s Inbox&#8221;<!-- \/a -->, <strong>(REFERENCE ICON) FURTHER READING <a href=\"http:\/\/articles.latimes.com\/2003\/may\/11\/business\/fi-spam11\">&#8220;Pandora&#8217;s Inbox&#8221;<\/a><\/strong> we&#8217;ve had to develop attention and information-management systems that prove crucial for surviving today&#8217;s communications-rich environment.<\/p>\n",
    "excerpt": "After all, spam &#8212; now estimated at more than 75% of e-mail traffic (REFERENCE ICON) According to the Spam Report, 2011. FURTHER READING Spam report: February 2011 &#8212; has been one of the major drivers of online innovation. To cope &hellip; <a href=\"http:\/\/book.hyko.org\/1970-09-03\/\">Continue reading <span class=\"meta-nav\">&rarr;<\/span><\/a>",
