    "id": 197804,
    "type": "post",
    "slug": "1970-09-04",
    "url": "http:\/\/book.hyko.org\/1970-09-04\/",
    "status": "publish",
    "title": "10 Ways SPAM Taught Us to Focus Our Attention &sect; 4",
    "title_plain": "10 Ways SPAM Taught Us to Focus Our Attention &sect; 4",
    "content": "<p>Spam is the vaccine for your attention span. It&#8217;s the toxin that has stimulated our immunity system&#8217;s defenses. Thanks to spam, we&#8217;ve had to find technical, social and personal ways of keeping our eyes on the 22% of e-mail that isn&#8217;t pure junk, and to avoid the 78% that is.<\/p>\n",
    "excerpt": "Spam is the vaccine for your attention span. It&#8217;s the toxin that has stimulated our immunity system&#8217;s defenses. Thanks to spam, we&#8217;ve had to find technical, social and personal ways of keeping our eyes on the 22% of e-mail that &hellip; <a href=\"http:\/\/book.hyko.org\/1970-09-04\/\">Continue reading <span class=\"meta-nav\">&rarr;<\/span><\/a>",
