    "title": "10 Ways You Can Help to Build the Internet &sect; 1",
    "title_plain": "10 Ways You Can Help to Build the Internet &sect; 1",
    "content": "<p>On November 22, 1977 a van drove onto Interstate 280 and into history. Most histories of the Internet begin with the ARPANET, the US Defense department network that gave birth to today&#8217;s Internet. But the true Internet began when that van used TCP to bridge between three networks: ARPANET, a satellite network and a packet radio network. It&#8217;s this networking of networks &#8212; or internetworking &#8212; that first demonstrated the future Internet.<\/p>\n",
