    "title": "10 Ways You Can Help to Build the Internet &sect; 2",
    "title_plain": "10 Ways You Can Help to Build the Internet &sect; 2",
    "content": "<p>It was <!-- a href=\"http:\/\/ed-thelen.org\/comp-hist\/CORE-3-1-SRI-TCP-IP.html\" -->only in 1996 that this moment was recognized<!-- \/a --> for its historical significance, <strong>(REFERENCE ICON) &#8220;The possible importance of &#8216;the van&#8217; began to surface sometime in 1996&#8230; when Vint Cart said in an interview that &#8220;SRI was the site of the first internet transmission.&#8221; FURTHER READING <a href=\"http:\/\/ed-thelen.org\/comp-hist\/CORE-3-1-SRI-TCP-IP.html\">The SRI Van<\/a><\/strong> and in 2007 it was celebrated with a <!-- a href=\"http:\/\/www.computerhistory.org\/events\/index.php?id=1191351626\" -->special event at the Computer History Museum<!-- \/a -->. <strong>(REFERENCE ICON) In November 2007, the Computer History Museum commemorated the 30th anniversary of the first TCP-based transmission between three dissimilar networks. FURTHER READING <a href=\"http:\/\/www.computerhistory.org\/press\/30th-anniversary-internet-milestone.html\">Computer History Museum and Web History Center Celebrate 30th Anniversary of Internet Milestone<\/a><\/strong> Reflecting on those early days of the Internet, Vint Cerf &#8212; part of the original van crew, and by 2007 the chief Internet evangelist for Google, was <!-- a href=\"http:\/\/www.zdnet.com\/news\/internet-van-helped-drive-evolution-of-the-web\/174749\" -->quoted in a news story<!-- \/a --> as saying: &#8220;A lot of people think the Internet just happened. But it was a lot of hard work.&#8221; <strong>ALEX: 404 ERROR &#8211; CAN&#8217;T FIND REFERENCED ARTICLE OR QUOTATION ANYWHERE. REMOVE QUOTE OR LEAVE IN UNATTRIBUTED?<\/strong><br \/>\nCerf may have been speaking in the past tense, but the work isn&#8217;t done: new technologies and standards are developed all the time. And these are still early days: of the <!--ALEX - THIS LINK IS 404. a href=\"http:\/\/www.vancouversun.com\/technology\/Number+Internet+users+worldwide+reaches+billion\/4177243\/story.html\" -->2 billion people online today<!-- \/a -->, <strong>(REFERENCE ICON) In January 2011, the United Nations announced that there were over 2 billion internet users worldwide. FURTHER READING <a href=\"http:\/\/www.google.com\/hostednews\/afp\/article\/ALeqM5iL3JD4qYM6YTkh7BSVMHUn2z7qFg\">Number of Internet users worldwide reaches 2 billion: UN<\/a><\/strong> only half were <!-- a href=\"http:\/\/www.internetworldstats.com\/pr\/edi022.htm\" -->online in 2006<!-- \/a -->. <strong>(REFERENCE ICON) According to Internet World Stats, there were just over 1 billion internet users worldwide in September 2006. FURTHER READING <a href=\"http:\/\/www.internetworldstats.com\/pr\/edi022.htm\">The 2006Q3 Internet Report<\/a><\/strong> You can reckon that we&#8217;ve still got lots of growth ahead, not just in how many of us are online but in what we do there and how we do it.<\/p>\n",
