    "title_plain": "Dittos Remind Us of the Pleasures of Obsolescence &sect; 4",
    "content": "<p>The lowly classroom handout is like a radar gun for the speed of change. I&#8217;m <!-- a href=\"http:\/\/alexlov.es\/1971\" -->not even 40 (yet)<!-- \/a -->, and I can play a very respectable game of &#8220;when I was a boy&#8230;.&#8221; OK, so sniffing mimeos isn&#8217;t quite as dramatic as walking three miles to school through the proverbial snowdrifts. But when my mother was 39, there were only three everyday technologies that had become obsolete in her lifetime: passenger ships, telegrams and pantyhose.<\/p>\n",
