    "title": "Dittos Remind Us of the Pleasures of Obsolescence &sect; 11",
    "title_plain": "Dittos Remind Us of the Pleasures of Obsolescence &sect; 11",
    "content": "<p>Without our visceral memories to connect us later we need visceral experiences to connect us now. My colleague <!-- a href=\"http:\/\/fullcirc.com\" -->Nancy White<!-- \/a --> introduced me to the idea of listening to a common piece of music at the beginning of a text chat session: it puts all the participants in the same mental space. You can open two bottles of the same wine, one in each city, while you Skype with a friend. We may even be able to <a href=\"http:\/\/news.cnet.com\/8301-17938_105-20020924-1.html\">tie our digital experiences to that most powerful of memory-triggers, scent<\/a>.(REFERENCE ICON) A team from Keio University Tokyo are developing technology that can print scents. FURTHER READING <a href=\"http:\/\/news.cnet.com\/8301-17938_105-20020924-1.html\">Hack turns Canon printer into a scent creator<\/a><\/p>\n",
    "excerpt": "Without our visceral memories to connect us later we need visceral experiences to connect us now. My colleague Nancy White introduced me to the idea of listening to a common piece of music at the beginning of a text chat &hellip; <a href=\"http:\/\/book.hyko.org\/1970-07-11\/\">Continue reading <span class=\"meta-nav\">&rarr;<\/span><\/a>",
