    "title_plain": "Finding Our Online Elders &sect; 4",
    "content": "<p>The first online moderator had almost no online experience to draw from. Einar Stefferud stepped into the job of moderating the world first email list &#8212; the world&#8217;s first online community! &#8212; MsgGroup, founded in 1975. MsgGroup&#8217;s members were literally inventing not only the conventions of online conversation, but the conventions of email itself &#8212; and as their conversation unfolded, it became clear that someone needed to assume the responsibility of gently moving discussion towards decision, resolving conflicts and answering questions from new members of the group.<\/p>\n",
    "excerpt": "The first online moderator had almost no online experience to draw from. Einar Stefferud stepped into the job of moderating the world first email list &#8212; the world&#8217;s first online community! &#8212; MsgGroup, founded in 1975. MsgGroup&#8217;s members were literally &hellip; <a href=\"http:\/\/book.hyko.org\/1970-06-04\/\">Continue reading <span class=\"meta-nav\">&rarr;<\/span><\/a>",
