    "content": "<p>In stepping into this role, Stefferud not only addressed the prosaic problems of how to add new members to the list or manage excess list traffic, but served as the prototype for what would become an essential &#8212; if often under appreciated &#8212; role in life online. The very term &#8220;moderator&#8221; implies that the chief purpose is to prevent unwanted behaviours; to moderate the worst excesses of online conversation. As Nancy White notes in her excellent history of online facilitation [LINK],<\/p>\n",
