    "title_plain": "Finding Our Online Elders &sect; 8",
    "content": "<p>In a online world that all too often buys into the self-mythology of the Internet as a totally new, Wild West-like frontier, it&#8217;s easy for us to dismiss the value of these online elders; to see them as superfluous now that we can have self-managing conversations via Twitter, Facebook and blogs &#8212; all platforms in which the online moderator is an invisible (if even existent) role.<\/p>\n",
    "excerpt": "In a online world that all too often buys into the self-mythology of the Internet as a totally new, Wild West-like frontier, it&#8217;s easy for us to dismiss the value of these online elders; to see them as superfluous now &hellip; <a href=\"http:\/\/book.hyko.org\/1970-06-08\/\">Continue reading <span class=\"meta-nav\">&rarr;<\/span><\/a>",
