    "title_plain": "Finding Our Online Elders &sect; 10",
    "content": "<p>The baby elders haven&#8217;t got it all figured out, however. There&#8217;s a reason that offline elders typically are drawn from the oldest members of the community: they&#8217;ve got a lifetime of wisdom to share, and have perhaps sanded off the edges of ego and urgency that sometimes keep people my age from engaging with kindness and integrity. They can be there for others, because they&#8217;ve already had their turn.<\/p>\n",
    "excerpt": "The baby elders haven&#8217;t got it all figured out, however. There&#8217;s a reason that offline elders typically are drawn from the oldest members of the community: they&#8217;ve got a lifetime of wisdom to share, and have perhaps sanded off the &hellip; <a href=\"http:\/\/book.hyko.org\/1970-06-10\/\">Continue reading <span class=\"meta-nav\">&rarr;<\/span><\/a>",
