    "title": "Finding Our Online Elders &sect; 13",
    "title_plain": "Finding Our Online Elders &sect; 13",
    "content": "<p>What would happen if we took those reservations seriously &#8212; if we actually listened to what older people say about how we are approaching our new lives online? What would happen if we made space for them in the conversation, and made space for their culture &#8212; our inherited cultural norms &#8212; as part of the Internet, rather than a now-deprecated relic? And what kind of online society would we be able to build if we brought the best of offline culture with us?<\/p>\n",
    "excerpt": "What would happen if we took those reservations seriously &#8212; if we actually listened to what older people say about how we are approaching our new lives online? What would happen if we made space for them in the conversation, &hellip; <a href=\"http:\/\/book.hyko.org\/1970-06-13\/\">Continue reading <span class=\"meta-nav\">&rarr;<\/span><\/a>",
