    "url": "http:\/\/book.hyko.org\/1970-04-02\/",
    "status": "publish",
    "title": "7 Rules for Rule-Breakers &sect; 2",
    "title_plain": "7 Rules for Rule-Breakers &sect; 2",
    "content": "<p>If that seems like a trivial online transgression in the era of <!-- a href=\"http:\/\/www.bittorrent.com\/\"-->BitTorrent<!-- \/a -->\u00a0<strong>(REFERENCE ICON)\u00a0BitTorrent is &#8220;a way to transfer files of just about any size quickly and efficiently. It works by breaking files up into small pieces. The file is downloaded piece by piece from one or many different sources. It&#8217;s efficient because you get faster downloads using a lot less bandwidth.&#8221; FURTHER READING Bittorrent.com<\/strong>, then you can thank Steve Wozniak, who blazed a trail for me twenty years before I discovered Homer&#8217;s voice. In 1973, Wozniak and his business partner Steve Jobs had just started selling &#8220;blue boxes&#8221;: devices that Wozniak had developed two years earlier for the purpose of making long-distance telephone calls for free.<strong>(REFERENCE ICON) One of the earliest phone phreakers, John Draper, (also known as Captain Crunch) introduced Wozniak to phreaking. By 1973, Wozniak and Steve Jobs were selling blue boxes out of their dorm rooms for $150 per box.\u00a0FURTHER READING\u00a0<a href=\"http:\/\/www.meme.ca\/Phreaks-of-Many-Colours-015913.php\">Phreaks of Many Colors<\/a>\u00a0<\/strong>(Note to The Kidz: Back in the day, you had to pay for a telephone call based on the distance between you and the person you were calling. I knew, them were some crazy times.)<\/p>\n",
    "excerpt": "If that seems like a trivial online transgression in the era of BitTorrent\u00a0(REFERENCE ICON)\u00a0BitTorrent is &#8220;a way to transfer files of just about any size quickly and efficiently. It works by breaking files up into small pieces. The file is &hellip; <a href=\"http:\/\/book.hyko.org\/1970-04-02\/\">Continue reading <span class=\"meta-nav\">&rarr;<\/span><\/a>",
