    "title_plain": "7 Rules for Rule-Breakers &sect; 7",
    "content": "<p>The irony is that while the Internet hates rules, it loves standards. Pretty much every fundamental aspect of how the Internet works, from which characters you can type to the way an online calendar entry is structured, is determined by an agreed-upon set of standards. <strong>(REFERENCE ICON)\u00a0<a href=\"http:\/\/www.rfc-editor.org\/rfcxx00.html\">Official Internet Protocol Standards<\/a><\/strong><\/p>\n",
    "excerpt": "The irony is that while the Internet hates rules, it loves standards. Pretty much every fundamental aspect of how the Internet works, from which characters you can type to the way an online calendar entry is structured, is determined by &hellip; <a href=\"http:\/\/book.hyko.org\/1970-04-07\/\">Continue reading <span class=\"meta-nav\">&rarr;<\/span><\/a>",
