    "content": "<p>You could say that my marriage began with a Palm Pilot. You might remember the  <!-- a href=\"http:\/\/www.cio.com\/article\/496839\/From_Palm_Pilot_to_Palm_Pre_A_Brief_History_of_Palm_s_Handhelds?page=2#slideshow\" -->second-generation Palm device<!--\/a -->, best known for its handwriting-based interface. (Ooh! Aah!) I got mine in 1997, at a time when a pocket-sized digital calendar, address book and notetaker still seemed like something worth showing off. And show it off I did, most often by\u00a0demonstrating <!-- a href=\"http:\/\/www-ai.ijs.si\/eliza\/eliza.html\" -->ELIZA<!-- \/a -->, a program that turned the Palm into a quasi-therapist. Give ELIZA a dilemma (&#8220;I can&#8217;t decide whether to finish grad school&#8221;) and ELIZA replied with a non-committal prompt (&#8220;Have you tried?&#8221;) aimed at continuing the conversation. <strong>SIDEBAR: Meet <a href=\"http:\/\/www-ai.ijs.si\/eliza\/eliza.html\">Eliza<\/a><\/strong><\/p>\n",
