    "title_plain": "ELIZA, IANA and the search for (in)finite attention online &sect; 4",
    "content": "<p>I was far from being ELIZA&#8217;s first patient. First created in 1966, ELIZA met her match in 1972, when she &#8220;treated&#8221; a fellow program, a paranoid schizophrenic personality named PARRY. Their most famous conversation took place at the first International Computer Communications Conference, an event specifically designed to introduce the <span style=\"text-decoration:underline\">ARPANET<\/span> to the general public. The wow factor at ICCC wasn&#8217;t (just) the spectacle of two computers talking to one another, but of two computers talking to one another remotely over a network chat connection. SIDEBAR: You can read a <a href=\"http:\/\/www.faqs.org\/rfcs\/rfc439.html\">transcript of ELIZA and PARRY in conversation<\/a>\u00a0just a few months before ICCC.<\/p>\n",
    "excerpt": "I was far from being ELIZA&#8217;s first patient. First created in 1966, ELIZA met her match in 1972, when she &#8220;treated&#8221; a fellow program, a paranoid schizophrenic personality named PARRY. Their most famous conversation took place at the first International &hellip; <a href=\"http:\/\/book.hyko.org\/1970-03-04\/\">Continue reading <span class=\"meta-nav\">&rarr;<\/span><\/a>",
