    "title_plain": "ELIZA, IANA and the search for (in)finite attention online &sect; 9",
    "content": "<p>The continued fascination with ELIZA and her descendants helps explain the persistence of our scarcity mindset. We fill in the gaps in ELIZA&#8217;s functionality, conspiring in the illusion that we&#8217;re talking to a &#8220;real&#8221; person, because it helps to meet our almost infinite need for the one truly finite resource: attention.<\/p>\n",
    "excerpt": "The continued fascination with ELIZA and her descendants helps explain the persistence of our scarcity mindset. We fill in the gaps in ELIZA&#8217;s functionality, conspiring in the illusion that we&#8217;re talking to a &#8220;real&#8221; person, because it helps to meet &hellip; <a href=\"http:\/\/book.hyko.org\/1970-03-09\/\">Continue reading <span class=\"meta-nav\">&rarr;<\/span><\/a>",
