    "title_plain": "ELIZA, IANA and the search for (in)finite attention online &sect; 11",
    "content": "<p>Indeed, the ELIZA effect is the solution to the world that IANA created. IANA gave us a world of infinite connectivity, which is the same thing as a world of infinite distractions and infinite exits. A world of 4.3 billion IP addresses is a world in which there are at least 4.3 billion things someone can pay attention to \u2013 but a world in which there is no more attention to go around. It&#8217;s a world in which it&#8217;s easy to feel neglected; a world in which we can easily become as narcissistic and paranoid as poor, virtual PARRY. Thank you, 1972.<\/p>\n",
    "excerpt": "Indeed, the ELIZA effect is the solution to the world that IANA created. IANA gave us a world of infinite connectivity, which is the same thing as a world of infinite distractions and infinite exits. A world of 4.3 billion &hellip; <a href=\"http:\/\/book.hyko.org\/1970-03-11\/\">Continue reading <span class=\"meta-nav\">&rarr;<\/span><\/a>",
