    "url": "http:\/\/book.hyko.org\/1970-03-12\/",
    "status": "publish",
    "title": "ELIZA, IANA and the search for (in)finite attention online &sect; 12",
    "title_plain": "ELIZA, IANA and the search for (in)finite attention online &sect; 12",
    "content": "<p>But the world you and I live in today is a world in which we get to choose between IANA and ELIZA. Do we face up to the reality of scarcity &#8212; whether it&#8217;s scarcity of attention, fuel, or IPv4 addresses &#8212; and find new ways to create abundance? Or do we create the illusion of abundance by settling for a simulation of the scarce resource we crave the most: the attention of our fellow human beings?<\/p>\n",
    "excerpt": "But the world you and I live in today is a world in which we get to choose between IANA and ELIZA. Do we face up to the reality of scarcity &#8212; whether it&#8217;s scarcity of attention, fuel, or IPv4 &hellip; <a href=\"http:\/\/book.hyko.org\/1970-03-12\/\">Continue reading <span class=\"meta-nav\">&rarr;<\/span><\/a>",
