    "title_plain": "ELIZA, IANA and the search for (in)finite attention online &sect; 18",
    "content": "<p>Once we separate our emotional need for human attention from our strategic need for machine attention (of which links are only the most simplistic example), it becomes possible for us to give and get the kind of attention we need online. By all means, follow a thousand people on Twitter: just be aware that even if all one thousand notice and retweet you, it&#8217;s going to help your SEO more than your self.<\/p>\n",
    "excerpt": "Once we separate our emotional need for human attention from our strategic need for machine attention (of which links are only the most simplistic example), it becomes possible for us to give and get the kind of attention we need &hellip; <a href=\"http:\/\/book.hyko.org\/1970-03-18\/\">Continue reading <span class=\"meta-nav\">&rarr;<\/span><\/a>",
