    "title_plain": "Where You At? &sect; 1",
    "content": "<p>To send the world&#8217;s first email in late 1971, programmer Ray Tomlinson had to marry two different technologies. By combining the capabilities of a program sending messages between users of a single computer with the capabilities for of a program for transferring files over a network, he was able to create a new program that allowed messages to be sent over a network.[get an email person to read this]<\/p>\n",
    "excerpt": "To send the world&#8217;s first email in late 1971, programmer Ray Tomlinson had to marry two different technologies. By combining the capabilities of a program sending messages between users of a single computer with the capabilities for of a program &hellip; <a href=\"http:\/\/book.hyko.org\/1970-02-01\/\">Continue reading <span class=\"meta-nav\">&rarr;<\/span><\/a>",
