    "title": "Where You At? &sect; 3",
    "title_plain": "Where You At? &sect; 3",
    "content": "<p>He soon settled on a combination of username + hostname, separated by the &#8220;@&#8221; sign. &#8220;I am frequently asked why I chose the at sign,&#8221; Tomlinson has written, &#8220;But the at sign just makes sense. The purpose of the at sign (in English) was to indicate a unit price (for example, 10 items @ $1.95). I used the at sign to indicate that the user was &#8220;at&#8221; some other host rather than being local.&#8221; [Tomlinson, Ray, \"The first network email\", http:\/\/openmap.bbn.com\/~tomlinso\/ray\/firstemailframe.html]<\/p>\n",
    "excerpt": "He soon settled on a combination of username + hostname, separated by the &#8220;@&#8221; sign. &#8220;I am frequently asked why I chose the at sign,&#8221; Tomlinson has written, &#8220;But the at sign just makes sense. The purpose of the at &hellip; <a href=\"http:\/\/book.hyko.org\/1970-02-03\/\">Continue reading <span class=\"meta-nav\">&rarr;<\/span><\/a>",
