    "title": "Where You At? &sect; 4",
    "title_plain": "Where You At? &sect; 4",
    "content": "<p>Tomlinson&#8217;s adoption of the @ symbol did more than simply meeting a technical need. By selecting &#8220;at&#8221; as the preposition that defines our relation to the network, Tomlinson established location as the defining metaphor for our relationship to the network, and redefined our notion of place. Today, the @ sign is ubiquitous &#8212; in email, on Twitter, as a text shorthand, and as an icon &#8212; but only refers to geography in the loosest or most intermittent way.<\/p>\n",
    "excerpt": "Tomlinson&#8217;s adoption of the @ symbol did more than simply meeting a technical need. By selecting &#8220;at&#8221; as the preposition that defines our relation to the network, Tomlinson established location as the defining metaphor for our relationship to the network, &hellip; <a href=\"http:\/\/book.hyko.org\/1970-02-04\/\">Continue reading <span class=\"meta-nav\">&rarr;<\/span><\/a>",
