    "title": "Where You At? &sect; 5",
    "title_plain": "Where You At? &sect; 5",
    "content": "<p>Relaxing the relationship between geography and location is a mixed blessing. As envisaged by Tomlinson, the @ sign is most often used to locate us in relationship to an email host &#8212; a relationship that often locates us in a specific business, social or geographic community. When I write you from my @ECUAD.ca address I am locating myself as part of the community at Emily Carr University; from my @socialsignal.com address I am located within my business. Even a gmail address can be a broad statement of my identity in relationship to a specific community: I&#8217;m geekier than a hotmail user, but less geeky than someone with their own domain name.<\/p>\n",
    "excerpt": "Relaxing the relationship between geography and location is a mixed blessing. As envisaged by Tomlinson, the @ sign is most often used to locate us in relationship to an email host &#8212; a relationship that often locates us in a &hellip; <a href=\"http:\/\/book.hyko.org\/1970-02-05\/\">Continue reading <span class=\"meta-nav\">&rarr;<\/span><\/a>",
