    "title_plain": "Where You At? &sect; 7",
    "content": "<p>In severing the necessary relationship between where we are situated and what we are attending to, we enable commitments and relationships based on common interest, affinities or identities. The emergence of networked diaspora communities, multinational social movements and niche fetish sites are all widely-noted facets of our newfound ability to connect with anyone, anywhere. It&#8217;s what we gravitate towards, remark on and delight in the Internet. It&#8217;s at the heart of how the Internet has changed our economy, our politics and our society.<\/p>\n",
    "excerpt": "In severing the necessary relationship between where we are situated and what we are attending to, we enable commitments and relationships based on common interest, affinities or identities. The emergence of networked diaspora communities, multinational social movements and niche fetish &hellip; <a href=\"http:\/\/book.hyko.org\/1970-02-07\/\">Continue reading <span class=\"meta-nav\">&rarr;<\/span><\/a>",
