    "title_plain": "Where You At? &sect; 9",
    "content": "<p>The fusion of @ and at points to the continued relevance of local community, even in a world that makes global community both feasible and meaningful. You may work in a purely virtual organization; you may read news and blog posts from around the world; you may even maintain a full and satisfying social life made up of Facebook and Twitter friends scattered around the world. But for anyone who stays on the grid, geographic community still matters: it&#8217;s where you buy your food, it&#8217;s where you rest your head, and it&#8217;s where you get outside and feel the earth under your feet.<\/p>\n",
    "excerpt": "The fusion of @ and at points to the continued relevance of local community, even in a world that makes global community both feasible and meaningful. You may work in a purely virtual organization; you may read news and blog &hellip; <a href=\"http:\/\/book.hyko.org\/1970-02-09\/\">Continue reading <span class=\"meta-nav\">&rarr;<\/span><\/a>",
