    "title": "Where You At? &sect; 10",
    "title_plain": "Where You At? &sect; 10",
    "content": "<p>Most important, it&#8217;s where you have live in-the-flesh interactions with other human beings. The sheer volume of people you will see, speak to or engage with in your office, your neighbourhood or your city make the community you live one of the most significant communities in your life. Where you live shapes not only who you interact with, but how you see yourself. Whether you&#8217;re an iconoclast who likes to stand out from the crowd, or a joiner who likes to adapt and fit in, your geographic community is the canvas against which your identity either blends or clashes. Where you are at is a crucial part of who you are.<\/p>\n",
    "excerpt": "Most important, it&#8217;s where you have live in-the-flesh interactions with other human beings. The sheer volume of people you will see, speak to or engage with in your office, your neighbourhood or your city make the community you live one &hellip; <a href=\"http:\/\/book.hyko.org\/1970-02-10\/\">Continue reading <span class=\"meta-nav\">&rarr;<\/span><\/a>",
