    "content": "<p>Where you are @, on the other hand, gives your geographically defined identity a new context. You may be a cradle-to-grave New Yorker, but you can now also be part of the Ethiopian diaspora community or the global community of Tom Waits fans. You can live in a uniformly Catholic town in Spain, but find an online oasis with your fellow Buddhists. You may live in a remote part of Montana, but you can still hold down a virtual job at Google.<\/p>\n",
