    "title_plain": "Where You At? &sect; 13",
    "content": "<p>That&#8217;s the route I&#8217;ve taken myself, and it means that where I&#8217;m at offline is frequently less comfortable than where I&#8217;m @ online. Online, I hang with progressive geek grammar nerd overachievers (oh yes, we&#8217;re a demographic), who both inspire and understand my fervour on subjects ranging from climate change and working motherhood to the Oxford comma and the best way to organize your Gmail rules. Offline, I live in a city (Vancouver, Canada) that is known for its outdoorsy mellowness: the result is that I regularly get the hairy eyeball for misdeeds like checking my email during a kid&#8217;s birthday party, or insisting on a third round of copyediting at work.<\/p>\n",
    "excerpt": "That&#8217;s the route I&#8217;ve taken myself, and it means that where I&#8217;m at offline is frequently less comfortable than where I&#8217;m @ online. Online, I hang with progressive geek grammar nerd overachievers (oh yes, we&#8217;re a demographic), who both inspire &hellip; <a href=\"http:\/\/book.hyko.org\/1970-02-13\/\">Continue reading <span class=\"meta-nav\">&rarr;<\/span><\/a>",
