    "title": "Where You At? &sect; 14",
    "title_plain": "Where You At? &sect; 14",
    "content": "<p>As the place where I mitigate my type A-ness with a countervailing ethos, my offline life is often less comfortable than my online life. Where I&#8217;m @ is where I get validation for my natural inclinations and affinities; where I&#8217;m at is where I get restrained and even reprimanded. That&#8217;s going to be the case for more and more of us, simply because it&#8217;s easier to find a community of affinity online than to pick up a houseful of possessions and move to geographic community of people like you.<\/p>\n",
    "excerpt": "As the place where I mitigate my type A-ness with a countervailing ethos, my offline life is often less comfortable than my online life. Where I&#8217;m @ is where I get validation for my natural inclinations and affinities; where I&#8217;m &hellip; <a href=\"http:\/\/book.hyko.org\/1970-02-14\/\">Continue reading <span class=\"meta-nav\">&rarr;<\/span><\/a>",
