    "content": "<p>&#8220;Three classes of communications systems were investigated as candidates for the ARPA Network: fully interconnected point to point leased lines, line switched (dial-up) service, and message switched (store and forward) service. For the kind of service required, it was decided and later verified that the message switched service provided the greater flexibility, higher effective bandwidth, and lower cost than the other two systems.&#8221;<\/p>\n",
