    "title_plain": "Creating an Archive and Roadmap of the Digital Revolution &sect; 4",
    "content": "<p>We read critiques of meta-blogging &#8212; &#8220;blogging about blogging&#8221; &#8212; where else? but <a href=\"http:\/\/gapingvoid.com\/2005\/03\/06\/the-death-of-metablogging\/\">on a blog<\/a>. We&#8217;re told to just use the Internet, already, <a href=\"http:\/\/jamesshelley.net\/2011\/03\/the-back-end-of-the-internet\/\">instead of discussing it<\/a>. No wonder that when people write about their own struggles with life online, they may feel like they have to bracket their self-reflection with <a href=\"http:\/\/uppercasewoman.com\/2009\/12\/16\/one-of-those-navelgazing-posts-about-the-internet\/\">an apology for navel-gazing<\/a>.<\/p>\n",
    "excerpt": "We read critiques of meta-blogging &#8212; &#8220;blogging about blogging&#8221; &#8212; where else? but on a blog. We&#8217;re told to just use the Internet, already, instead of discussing it. No wonder that when people write about their own struggles with life &hellip; <a href=\"http:\/\/book.hyko.org\/1970-01-04\/\">Continue reading <span class=\"meta-nav\">&rarr;<\/span><\/a>",
