    "title_plain": "Creating an Archive and Roadmap of the Digital Revolution &sect; 6",
    "content": "<p>Our online reflections about the Internet create a roadmap in a very literal sense. You&#8217;d be hard-pressed to find an aspect of online life that can&#8217;t be more readily navigated thanks to the self-documentation of some previous Internet user. Want to register a domain name? Someone will tell you <a href=\"http:\/\/blogsessive.com\/domain-names\/how-to-register-a-domain-name-for-your-blog\/\">how to do it<\/a>, and <a href=\"http:\/\/www.problogger.net\/archives\/2006\/02\/16\/choosing-the-domain-name-for-your-blog\/\">what makes a good one<\/a>. Hoping to develop an appealingly wry online persona? You can learn <a href=\"http:\/\/mashable.com\/2012\/02\/08\/funny-twitter\/\">how to be funny on Twitter<\/a>. Worried about how much time you spend on your smartphone? You can learn <a href=\"http:\/\/www.huffingtonpost.com\/susan-conley\/smartphone-addiction-_b_1407091.html\">how other people have tried to manage their own smartphone compulsion<\/a>.<\/p>\n",
    "excerpt": "Our online reflections about the Internet create a roadmap in a very literal sense. You&#8217;d be hard-pressed to find an aspect of online life that can&#8217;t be more readily navigated thanks to the self-documentation of some previous Internet user. Want &hellip; <a href=\"http:\/\/book.hyko.org\/1970-01-06\/\">Continue reading <span class=\"meta-nav\">&rarr;<\/span><\/a>",
