    "title": "Creating an Archive and Roadmap of the Digital Revolution &sect; 7",
    "title_plain": "Creating an Archive and Roadmap of the Digital Revolution &sect; 7",
    "content": "<p>If all these &#8220;how to do it&#8221; and &#8220;here&#8217;s how I do it&#8221; posts are helpful in sharing what we know, they&#8217;re even more helpful in sharing what we don&#8217;t know. Precisely because the Internet has lowered the bar on publishing &#8212; establishing a culture of online sharing in which it&#8217;s ok to post even what&#8217;s half-baked or tentative &#8212; it allows us to disclose and access the ways we&#8217;re groping in the dark. We don&#8217;t know what we&#8217;re doing online, yet; we&#8217;re making it up as we go along. Seeing that other people don&#8217;t know what they&#8217;re doing, either &#8212; and yet, are brave or foolish enough to share that very state of not knowing &#8212; makes the online world less daunting. It gives us permission to explore, experiment and err.<\/p>\n",
    "excerpt": "If all these &#8220;how to do it&#8221; and &#8220;here&#8217;s how I do it&#8221; posts are helpful in sharing what we know, they&#8217;re even more helpful in sharing what we don&#8217;t know. Precisely because the Internet has lowered the bar on &hellip; <a href=\"http:\/\/book.hyko.org\/1970-01-07\/\">Continue reading <span class=\"meta-nav\">&rarr;<\/span><\/a>",
