    "title_plain": "Creating an Archive and Roadmap of the Digital Revolution &sect; 10",
    "content": "<p>All the missteps, uncertainties, internal struggles and victorious achievements compose the archive of our transition to the digital. There is no human revolution that comes close in the comprehensiveness of its documentation: look back to upheavals as recent as the civil rights movement or the collapse of the Soviet Union, and the historical record is already only partial. We are part of the world&#8217;s first fully self-documenting revolution, and it is the work of the revolution itself &#8212; its code, its academic papers, its anxious blog posts &#8212; that builds the archive.<\/p>\n",
